description:
The Mountain necklace features hand-cut brass peaks on a brass rope chain.

Laurel Hill makes jewelry inspired by the form and function of primitive jewelry, the connection between adornment and a belief system.  She cuts, files, hammers, stamps, and polishes every piece by hand in her Normaltown studio.  Born and raised in Georgia, she has lived in Athens since 1999.

description:

About 7 mm in diameter

Laurel Hill makes jewelry inspired by the form and function of primitive jewelry, the connection between adornment and a belief system.  She cuts, files, hammers, stamps, and polishes every piece by hand in her Normaltown studio.  Born and raised in Georgia, she has lived in Athens since 1999.  

These earrings were inspired by Laurel's friend Cheree.

name: Arya Earrings by Laurel Hill
description:
These brass earrings were inspired by Arya from Game of Thrones and Laurel's favorite pair of vintage earrings. Each piece is cut, filed, hammered, oxidized, and polished by hand, then coated with a layer of museum wax to preserve the patina. The findings and handmade earwires are sterling silver, and the back is marked with a crescent moon and her initials, LH.

From top to bottom, including the earwires, they hang 3.5 inches (9 cm), and they're 5/8" (1.5 cm) wide. These are made from 20 gauge brass, so they have a bit of weight to them. 

Laurel Hill makes jewelry inspired by the form and function of primitive jewelry, the connection between adornment and a belief system.  She cuts, files, hammers, stamps, and polishes every piece by hand in her Normaltown studio.  Born and raised in Georgia, she has lived in Athens since 1999.

name: Falcon Talon Necklace by Chelsea Lea
description:
Chelsea Ray Lea is a true Athenian born and raised in downtown Athens Georgia.
She is inspired by the environment, found objects, and the geometrical organization of forms.
As a descendant of many talented metal smiths Chelsea plans to continue to explore the vast
territory and processes in jewelry design. The medium of jewelry design truly fuels Chelsea's
appetite of curiosity, wonder, and fascination. 

This falcon talon necklace is a unique piece made using the lost wax process. Chelsea took a mold of a real falcon talon and used it to create a wax mold. She then injects molten bronze into the mold to creat the metal talon. After the metal has been cast, it must be cleaned, filed, sanded, soldered, and polished creating the intricate and beautiful pendant. 

Chain Length: 16.5 in

Take a bit of nature with you wherever you go with Chelsea's original piece of wearable art.

The talon is hung from a 14 KT, yellow gold filled, lever back ear wire.

Take a bit of nature with you wherever you go with Chelsea's original piece of wearable art.

name: Slate Letter Envelope Locket With Miniature Arrow Drawing
description:
When Missy was little, she learned to draw from Ed Emberly's books. She made my first zine when she was a teenager and has been drawing and making things ever since! She studied graphic design, but her true love is art. By day she works as a surface designer and a cartoonist, and by night she loves to draw and create things.

"You’re a rider on the stormy sea
What do you get for curiosity?
I am the girl with the feather heart
That the birds flew down and pecked apart."

These are lyrics to Missy’s favorite song by one of my favorite singers, Mary Timony. This song was the inspiration for her Loved Letter Envelope Locket.

Her Loved Letter Envelope Locket is made from an antique style envelope charm. Tucked away inside this charm is a miniature original drawing of a feather or an arrow on one side, and a heart on the other. This is drawn on heavy watercolor paper that is dyed with tea to give it a weathered look. Each charm is unique, so expect variations on the envelope locket.

The envelope locket measures about .75 inch wide and about .5 inches tall when closed. The charm is attached to a chain that is 18 inches in length that she put together herself with antique brass patina findings.

Each one is unique and special miniature work of art, a lovely treasure to wear around your neck!

name: Blue Maple Earrings by Cinnabar Lounge
description:
Ashley Robison, creator of Cinnabar Lounge, makes earrings, rings, bracelets, necklaces and antiqued framed earring displays.

She is married and lives in Athens, GA. She has a degree in Philosophy and has a varied and rich work and craft history. She apprentices in carpentry and works as a stagehand part time. She is also an Education Specialist with the University of Georgia.

She likes rich, dark things...like velvet, David Lynch films and Edward Gorey. She likes strange flowers, natures oddities, colors that shouldn't go together.

She obsesses over textile prints, Vera scarves and 80's toys. 

Ashley sees the world in minute detail. Always searching for balance and intricacy in her designs, she will continually produce a blissful cache of petite botanical earrings while hoping ever so much to charm you over and over again!

These earrings are made from pressed Czech glass maple beads, antiqued copper filigree bead caps, raw copper spacers and tiny Czech glass seed beads in sky blue. Set on antiqued copper findings.

name: Community Made T-Shirt - Don Chambers
description:
This shirt was designed by Don Chambers.

Don moved to Athens, Georgia in 1988 from Florence, South Caroline, where he grew up singing in a Plymouth Brethren church. In Athens, he fronted the band Vaudeville, an experimental punk trio in the 90’s before forming GOAT in 2001. Of his music, Rolling Stone writer Jenny Eliscu wrote, “Chambers . . . is one of Athens most underrated songwriters, and deals out tales of whiskey, heartbreak, and woe with his banjo.” Chambers is also a visual artist and designer and received his MFA in printmaking and painting from the University of Georgia. HE continues to do design work for his own band as well as other clients. Don is married to Sanni Baumgaertner, owner of Community.
